WEBVTT

1
00:01:26.367 --> 00:01:27.984
I'm leaving.

2
00:01:28.452 --> 00:01:29.886
OK.

3
00:01:31.655 --> 00:01:33.723
Don't forget to feed Oscar.

4
00:01:40.130 --> 00:01:42.099
Have fun while I'm gone.

5
00:01:46.403 --> 00:01:48.505
Why is Oscar so calm?

6
00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:51.641
Will he be hungry?

7
00:02:07.300 --> 00:02:09.025
Why not...

8
00:02:12.438 --> 00:02:14.931
Did you feed Oscar?

9
00:02:24.634 --> 00:02:26.610
I dislike that woman.

10
00:02:34.567 --> 00:02:36.186
Dad,

11
00:02:39.842 --> 00:02:42.492
Can you end the relationship with her?

12
00:02:50.492 --> 00:02:52.269
If you don't...

13
00:02:56.701 --> 00:02:59.075
Should I go back to mom?

14
00:03:09.953 --> 00:03:15.159
Before I felt tired
but satisfied when I finished working,

15
00:03:15.159 --> 00:03:17.494
now you have to be very careful
with the director.

16
00:03:17.494 --> 00:03:19.496
How uncomfortable.

17
00:03:19.496 --> 00:03:22.200
It's true, we have fewer pregnant women.

18
00:03:22.200 --> 00:03:24.640
I like this silence.

19
00:03:24.640 --> 00:03:27.137
this silence

20
00:03:27.137 --> 00:03:30.140
could mean less staff.

21
00:03:30.140 --> 00:03:31.841
They could do without us.

22
00:03:32.350 --> 00:03:36.213
We are discouraged, but with energy to spare,

23
00:03:36.213 --> 00:03:37.715
Shall we have dinner together?

24
00:03:37.715 --> 00:03:38.782
- Good idea.
- Yes, let's go.

25
00:03:38.782 --> 00:03:39.950
I sign up.

26
00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:41.919
- Where to?
- I want guts.

27
00:03:41.919 --> 00:03:43.667
Me, lamb skewers.

28
00:03:43.667 --> 00:03:45.034
- How many rounds?
- Hello, Do Hyun.

29
00:03:45.034 --> 00:03:46.334
- At least three rounds.
- Of course.

30
00:03:46.334 --> 00:03:48.500
- The first, skewers.
- Tripe and skewers.

31
00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:50.694
I'm about to leave work.

32
00:03:52.229 --> 00:03:54.731
Do Hyun, are you drunk? At this time?

33
00:03:55.601 --> 00:03:57.200
We're going to have a lot of fun.

34
00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:25.629
Do Hyun.

35
00:04:41.612 --> 00:04:43.280
Are you OK?

36
00:04:49.253 --> 00:04:50.754
I'm sorry.

37
00:04:54.558 --> 00:04:56.793
Do you want to walk a little?

38
00:05:08.639 --> 00:05:10.340
Daniel told me he was fine.

39
00:05:12.542 --> 00:05:14.210
It was what he always told me...

40
00:05:16.384 --> 00:05:18.581
which was fine.

41
00:05:20.034 --> 00:05:21.418
I...

42
00:05:22.300 --> 00:05:24.915
It is obvious that there is no way

43
00:05:24.915 --> 00:05:26.623
that it was okay.

44
00:05:30.068 --> 00:05:31.828
But, the truth is, I didn't know.

45
00:05:36.635 --> 00:05:38.668
Of course you didn't know.

46
00:05:40.395 --> 00:05:42.505
How to know?

47
00:05:43.895 --> 00:05:46.976
They hide it at all costs,

48
00:05:47.678 --> 00:05:50.880
They don't say a word.

49
00:05:58.620 --> 00:06:00.334
I...

50
00:06:00.334 --> 00:06:02.959
I want to get along with Daniel.

51
00:06:10.034 --> 00:06:11.568
That?

52
00:06:11.568 --> 00:06:13.294
Do you think it won't be possible?

53
00:06:13.294 --> 00:06:14.738
No...

54
00:06:15.539 --> 00:06:17.107
I...

55
00:06:18.475 --> 00:06:21.111
Honestly, I don't know what to do.

56
00:06:25.015 --> 00:06:26.783
I will do it.

57
00:06:29.495 --> 00:06:33.423
Daniel has his times.

58
00:06:34.491 --> 00:06:37.927
I don't know when or how it will be,

59
00:06:40.009 --> 00:06:43.233
but I will look for the opportunity.

60
00:06:44.801 --> 00:06:47.303
Who knows?
It could be sooner than we expect.

61
00:07:01.685 --> 00:07:03.653
Seriously...

62
00:07:04.955 --> 00:07:07.001
I didn't expect

63
00:07:07.001 --> 00:07:09.292
that you said that

64
00:07:11.950 --> 00:07:14.131
Daniel's feelings...

65
00:07:14.131 --> 00:07:15.601
I can't do anything

66
00:07:15.601 --> 00:07:17.901
about it

67
00:07:19.069 --> 00:07:21.471
and I know it will be difficult for you.

68
00:07:24.508 --> 00:07:26.943
I can't stop thinking about how you could leave me.

69
00:07:28.050 --> 00:07:30.847
What if you abandon me because of this?

70
00:07:33.867 --> 00:07:37.500
You are quite an artist.

71
00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:40.123
Oh really.

72
00:07:46.663 --> 00:07:48.698
[Catholic Church]

73
00:07:48.698 --> 00:07:51.667
Two adults without commitments

74
00:07:51.667 --> 00:07:54.137
They spent the night together.

75
00:07:54.137 --> 00:07:56.272
It was with the consent of both.

76
00:07:57.834 --> 00:07:59.943
What is the problem?

77
00:08:01.204 --> 00:08:03.012
The truth...

78
00:08:04.233 --> 00:08:06.149
It's not a problem.

79
00:08:06.149 --> 00:08:08.051
Was it a one-time affair?

80
00:08:08.051 --> 00:08:10.167
No!

81
00:08:10.167 --> 00:08:13.690
- It wasn't an adventure.
- So, it must be love.

82
00:08:14.758 --> 00:08:16.334
Well,

83
00:08:16.334 --> 00:08:18.601
It's not exactly love either.

84
00:08:18.601 --> 00:08:20.330
So...

85
00:08:21.031 --> 00:08:24.668
what is it that torments you

86
00:08:24.668 --> 00:08:26.236
at this moment?

87
00:08:26.938 --> 00:08:31.208
We've known each other since kindergarten.

88
00:08:31.208 --> 00:08:32.742
AND?

89
00:08:33.425 --> 00:08:35.400
Well...

90
00:08:35.400 --> 00:08:36.880
if this doesn't work,

91
00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:38.915
I'm afraid it will ruin

92
00:08:38.915 --> 00:08:40.550
a friendship of 20 years.

93
00:08:40.550 --> 00:08:42.652
So what if it turns out like this?

94
00:08:44.144 --> 00:08:45.845
Sorry?

95
00:08:45.845 --> 00:08:49.859
I asked you what's wrong
if a 20 year friendship ends.

96
00:08:51.801 --> 00:08:53.363
Well...

97
00:08:57.467 --> 00:08:59.936
[Faithful]

98
00:08:59.936 --> 00:09:01.838
Busy.

99
00:09:05.015 --> 00:09:06.375
Hey,

100
00:09:06.375 --> 00:09:08.112
Get out of here.

101
00:09:08.112 --> 00:09:09.379
That?

102
00:09:10.314 --> 00:09:12.415
I told you to get out.

103
00:09:20.057 --> 00:09:23.126
Aren't you old enough to be beaten like that?

104
00:09:23.861 --> 00:09:26.315
They didn't hit me, father.

105
00:09:26.315 --> 00:09:28.431
It was an act of punishment and revenge.

106
00:09:28.431 --> 00:09:30.300
My God.

107
00:09:30.300 --> 00:09:34.004
Like wood, like wood, they are equal.

108
00:09:34.004 --> 00:09:35.305
That?

109
00:09:36.504 --> 00:09:39.609
Call me "dude," like old times.

110
00:09:41.901 --> 00:09:43.680
Okay, friend.

111
00:09:44.781 --> 00:09:46.934
So,

112
00:09:46.934 --> 00:09:49.824
You are between love and friendship, right?

113
00:09:49.824 --> 00:09:51.921
The same old cliché.

114
00:09:52.667 --> 00:09:56.259
I don't think it comes down to that, but...

115
00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:59.100
Do you know what happened between Jun Kyung and me?

116
00:09:59.100 --> 00:10:01.331
at school, right?

117
00:10:03.084 --> 00:10:06.102
You call that a relationship?

118
00:10:07.014 --> 00:10:08.968
In any case,

119
00:10:08.968 --> 00:10:10.340
He didn't like you.

120
00:10:10.340 --> 00:10:13.543
You harassed her and spread rumors,

121
00:10:13.543 --> 00:10:15.378
In the end my mom threw water on you.

122
00:10:15.378 --> 00:10:17.581
I was at my best, full of energy,

123
00:10:17.581 --> 00:10:21.284
why did I give up on Jun Kyung
instead of enduring that humiliation?

124
00:10:21.934 --> 00:10:23.325
That?

125
00:10:25.655 --> 00:10:28.324
I chose friendship then.

126
00:10:28.858 --> 00:10:31.894
It was between love and friendship.

127
00:10:33.828 --> 00:10:36.733
I did it for the sake of a great friendship.

128
00:10:38.534 --> 00:10:40.170
Hey.

129
00:10:40.170 --> 00:10:43.706
- You were never his type.
- Be quiet.

130
00:10:45.599 --> 00:10:48.111
Friendship, yes, of course.

131
00:10:48.111 --> 00:10:50.947
You just lacked courage and confidence,

132
00:10:51.780 --> 00:10:55.818
Yours is nothing more than a loser's excuse.

133
00:10:58.121 --> 00:11:00.223
Do you really not like it?

134
00:11:04.157 --> 00:11:06.696
If you don't like it, why do you care?

135
00:11:38.728 --> 00:11:40.797
It doesn't have a single scratch.

136
00:11:42.432 --> 00:11:44.701
What an idiot.

137
00:11:45.369 --> 00:11:46.830
Listen.

138
00:11:47.904 --> 00:11:49.941
It's sudden,

139
00:11:49.941 --> 00:11:51.975
but our publicist, Hwang Beom Jun,

140
00:11:51.975 --> 00:11:55.745
He just handed in his resignation.

141
00:11:55.745 --> 00:11:58.081
He feels guilty,
so tonight he invites.

142
00:11:58.081 --> 00:12:00.599
Let's all go out after work.

143
00:12:00.599 --> 00:12:03.320
Let's make him spend a lot of money before he leaves.

144
00:12:03.320 --> 00:12:05.588
He said he would treat us to the most expensive!

145
00:12:05.588 --> 00:12:08.157
See you! I invite you to dinner!

146
00:12:12.028 --> 00:12:13.664
It's great,

147
00:12:13.664 --> 00:12:17.834
you give up for love,
You go to Europe and you don't know when you'll come back.

148
00:12:19.102 --> 00:12:22.489
I wish I was your age, Beom Jun.

149
00:12:22.489 --> 00:12:24.601
You still have time,

150
00:12:24.601 --> 00:12:26.709
boss.

151
00:12:27.243 --> 00:12:28.978
I don't have the courage or the talent.

152
00:12:28.978 --> 00:12:30.049
It's not about talent,

153
00:12:30.049 --> 00:12:32.582
only people who work for fun
can do it.

154
00:12:32.582 --> 00:12:35.285
Where in Europe will you go?

155
00:12:35.285 --> 00:12:39.388
He said he wants to visit Estonia,

156
00:12:39.952 --> 00:12:42.792
so we will start with the Baltic States.

157
00:12:43.827 --> 00:12:44.913
The Baltic States.

158
00:12:44.913 --> 00:12:47.231
I've only heard about them in books.

159
00:12:47.231 --> 00:12:49.165
Where are the Baltic States?

160
00:12:51.801 --> 00:12:53.370
- Are you leaving?
- Are you leaving already?

161
00:12:53.370 --> 00:12:54.771
I think so.

162
00:13:12.968 --> 00:13:15.425
I tell you it's not that.

163
00:13:15.425 --> 00:13:16.434
Enough.

164
00:13:16.434 --> 00:13:18.828
- I'm sick of hearing that.
- A cake!

165
00:13:18.828 --> 00:13:19.634
That?

166
00:13:19.634 --> 00:13:21.567
See? That's the spirit.

167
00:13:21.567 --> 00:13:23.534
After all, it's a farewell party.

168
00:13:23.534 --> 00:13:25.701
- Oh really?
- Did you go get a cake?

169
00:13:27.937 --> 00:13:29.518
Congratulations.

170
00:13:29.518 --> 00:13:32.858
Have a nice trip to Europe
with your girlfriend.

171
00:13:32.858 --> 00:13:35.211
Thank you...

172
00:13:42.786 --> 00:13:44.253
True...

173
00:13:45.488 --> 00:13:49.058
you are only faithful to your feelings,
I'm the idiot.

174
00:13:49.626 --> 00:13:51.194
No!

175
00:13:51.867 --> 00:13:54.023
- That?
- That?

176
00:13:54.567 --> 00:13:55.767
- What was that?
- What's happening?

177
00:13:55.767 --> 00:13:58.067
Why did he do that?

178
00:13:58.834 --> 00:14:01.567
For Mrs. Oh Mi Ja's 80th birthday.

179
00:14:01.567 --> 00:14:03.173
Understood.

180
00:14:03.173 --> 00:14:05.675
I'm not that stingy.

181
00:14:05.675 --> 00:14:08.277
If you order more than 300 towels,
I include everything at no additional cost.

182
00:14:13.483 --> 00:14:15.953
Keep your voice down, I'm talking on the phone.

183
00:14:15.953 --> 00:14:18.254
No! Yes, go ahead.

184
00:14:18.254 --> 00:14:19.389
Good.

185
00:14:19.389 --> 00:14:23.559
We will do it for you. Fine, thanks.

186
00:14:25.095 --> 00:14:26.529
-Jin Ho!
- That?

187
00:14:26.529 --> 00:14:28.531
You didn't say you were coming. What brings you here?

188
00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:31.701
Hello.

189
00:14:37.554 --> 00:14:38.339
Hello.

190
00:14:38.339 --> 00:14:40.895
You got my message, right?

191
00:14:40.895 --> 00:14:42.136
Yes.

192
00:14:42.136 --> 00:14:44.447
Grey, pink and white, a hundred of each.

193
00:14:44.447 --> 00:14:46.783
Yes, have them ready for the 15th.

194
00:14:46.783 --> 00:14:48.719
Thank you.

195
00:14:48.719 --> 00:14:50.915
Please understand her.

196
00:14:50.915 --> 00:14:52.890
You know how it is.

197
00:14:52.890 --> 00:14:54.434
What's wrong with him?

198
00:14:54.434 --> 00:14:56.158
It's the best.

199
00:14:57.427 --> 00:15:01.335
Did all the good people die?

200
00:15:01.335 --> 00:15:05.735
I'm not asking it to be soft like a new towel.

201
00:15:06.604 --> 00:15:08.199
However,

202
00:15:08.199 --> 00:15:10.306
it shouldn't be rough

203
00:15:10.306 --> 00:15:12.642
like a dish towel.

204
00:15:14.244 --> 00:15:16.013
What scrubbing towel?

205
00:15:16.013 --> 00:15:17.480
You scared me.

206
00:15:18.948 --> 00:15:20.483
When did you arrive?

207
00:15:20.483 --> 00:15:21.317
And the store?

208
00:15:21.317 --> 00:15:23.719
It's empty. You stay, hurry up.

209
00:15:24.239 --> 00:15:25.574
That?

210
00:15:27.124 --> 00:15:28.824
OK.

211
00:15:31.762 --> 00:15:34.297
I'll come visit you soon.

212
00:15:53.650 --> 00:15:58.554
When he brought you home
to announce that they would get married,

213
00:16:00.189 --> 00:16:04.026
Everyone opposed it, it was chaos.

214
00:16:06.573 --> 00:16:09.174
- It must have been like that.
- Yes.

215
00:16:09.174 --> 00:16:11.634
Remember how old they were back then.

216
00:16:13.294 --> 00:16:15.934
But do you know that I was the only one

217
00:16:15.934 --> 00:16:17.308
who approved it?

218
00:16:17.308 --> 00:16:18.874
Of course, I know.

219
00:16:43.357 --> 00:16:46.971
My sister asked me why I supported them.

220
00:16:46.971 --> 00:16:49.071
Do you know what I answered?

221
00:16:52.479 --> 00:16:56.179
I told him you were vulgar,
so other girls wouldn't like you.

222
00:16:56.179 --> 00:16:57.834
That is,

223
00:16:57.834 --> 00:17:01.050
You couldn't cheat on her with anyone.

224
00:17:03.784 --> 00:17:06.237
I don't know what to say in this situation,

225
00:17:06.237 --> 00:17:08.257
but, seriously,

226
00:17:08.257 --> 00:17:09.325
- it's a misunderstanding.
- No.

227
00:17:09.325 --> 00:17:12.496
You didn't have the guts

228
00:17:12.496 --> 00:17:15.297
to deceive my sister while she was alive.

229
00:17:16.567 --> 00:17:19.634
How could I not know?

230
00:17:23.249 --> 00:17:25.934
My husband does nothing but laugh

231
00:17:25.934 --> 00:17:28.177
when clients don't pay you.

232
00:17:28.177 --> 00:17:31.313
I've seen him do that for over 20 years.

233
00:17:32.901 --> 00:17:35.564
Maybe I'm selfish

234
00:17:35.564 --> 00:17:39.422
But I see my husband and my blood boils.

235
00:17:40.580 --> 00:17:42.425
Yes...

236
00:17:43.434 --> 00:17:47.163
he would have had an accident
and it would have ended like this...

237
00:17:48.632 --> 00:17:52.468
If I had to change his diapers
for seven years

238
00:17:53.634 --> 00:17:56.339
and I would have had to endure that temper,

239
00:17:56.339 --> 00:18:00.200
no way

240
00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:02.611
I could have done it.

241
00:18:04.918 --> 00:18:07.850
But he probably did,

242
00:18:08.860 --> 00:18:10.653
because he is a fool.

243
00:18:14.752 --> 00:18:17.760
Although we are family,

244
00:18:17.760 --> 00:18:20.629
I only thought about my poor sister.

245
00:18:21.297 --> 00:18:23.532
I didn't think about how difficult...

246
00:18:25.500 --> 00:18:26.503
that was for you.

247
00:18:26.503 --> 00:18:28.671
I'm sorry.

248
00:18:29.434 --> 00:18:31.207
No, it's okay.

249
00:18:54.965 --> 00:18:58.234
I still can't congratulate you on that woman.

250
00:18:58.935 --> 00:19:03.706
I won't do it until the day I die.

251
00:19:06.100 --> 00:19:09.545
But thanks

252
00:19:10.701 --> 00:19:12.748
for taking care of my sister.

253
00:19:15.619 --> 00:19:18.154
Thank you so much.

254
00:19:35.505 --> 00:19:38.968
- May you get home safely.
- Bye bye.

255
00:19:38.968 --> 00:19:41.143
Stop babbling.

256
00:19:42.678 --> 00:19:45.449
- Is it fun?
- Yes, it's fun!

257
00:19:45.449 --> 00:19:47.416
Let's go for the second round!

258
00:20:06.026 --> 00:20:08.504
Why do I always find you sitting here?

259
00:20:09.786 --> 00:20:12.174
Don't you have anywhere else to go?

260
00:20:13.210 --> 00:20:15.244
Don't you respect my house?

261
00:20:17.357 --> 00:20:18.981
Why...

262
00:20:19.701 --> 00:20:21.452
are you so irritable?

263
00:20:21.452 --> 00:20:23.152
What are you doing here?

264
00:20:25.656 --> 00:20:26.787
What happened to your face?

265
00:20:26.787 --> 00:20:28.757
I asked you what you are doing here.

266
00:20:34.443 --> 00:20:38.100
I thought I should apologize.

267
00:20:42.230 --> 00:20:44.443
Apologize for what?

268
00:20:44.443 --> 00:20:45.975
I just broke up

269
00:20:46.934 --> 00:20:49.878
with Sun...

270
00:20:52.316 --> 00:20:54.250
- and...
- Forget it.

271
00:20:56.023 --> 00:20:58.487
My feelings belong to me.

272
00:20:58.487 --> 00:21:00.689
I don't expect anything from you.

273
00:21:03.519 --> 00:21:05.761
You don't have to say anything else.

274
00:21:08.098 --> 00:21:09.665
Alright.

275
00:21:10.868 --> 00:21:12.499
Well,

276
00:21:12.499 --> 00:21:14.203
there is something else.

277
00:21:15.406 --> 00:21:16.872
What's happening?

278
00:21:17.387 --> 00:21:19.975
-Whatever I can do...
- Tell them.

279
00:21:21.701 --> 00:21:23.712
Tell them you will do the internship.

280
00:21:24.927 --> 00:21:26.774
- That?
- You were sorry.

281
00:21:26.774 --> 00:21:29.151
You didn't do anything before your mother died.

282
00:21:30.853 --> 00:21:33.589
You know I had something to do with that, right?

283
00:21:34.757 --> 00:21:37.100
So take back the chance

284
00:21:37.100 --> 00:21:39.128
and invite me to eat accordingly.

285
00:21:50.107 --> 00:21:51.607
Anything else.

286
00:21:54.068 --> 00:21:56.712
Stop doubting everything.

287
00:21:57.513 --> 00:22:01.083
There are those who quit their jobs
and they are proud of it.

288
00:22:01.083 --> 00:22:04.553
They break up because they feel like it and go to Europe.

289
00:22:05.147 --> 00:22:07.022
Look at us.

290
00:22:08.534 --> 00:22:11.060
Why are we so idiots?

291
00:22:11.601 --> 00:22:13.128
Good heavens!

292
00:22:55.383 --> 00:22:57.573
<i>You don't know how happy I am...</i>

293
00:23:00.611 --> 00:23:02.144
<i>that you have come...</i>

294
00:23:04.133 --> 00:23:06.281
<i>to see me.</i>

295
00:23:39.200 --> 00:23:40.849
Daniel!

296
00:23:49.193 --> 00:23:51.871
I came because I have something to tell you.

297
00:24:02.634 --> 00:24:04.045
No!

298
00:24:08.344 --> 00:24:09.345
Child!

299
00:24:09.345 --> 00:24:12.214
Watch where you're going!

300
00:24:12.214 --> 00:24:15.684
What are you doing? He fell and hurt himself.

301
00:24:17.143 --> 00:24:18.627
I didn't hit him.

302
00:24:18.627 --> 00:24:21.523
He fell alone.

303
00:24:21.523 --> 00:24:23.503
You said it, it's a boy.

304
00:24:23.503 --> 00:24:26.796
You should have asked him if he was okay.

305
00:24:26.796 --> 00:24:29.166
Cars pass by here,

306
00:24:29.166 --> 00:24:31.163
I shouldn't be doing that.

307
00:24:31.163 --> 00:24:32.435
Who are you?

308
00:24:32.435 --> 00:24:35.204
Are you his mother?

309
00:24:35.204 --> 00:24:36.444
Yes.

310
00:24:38.522 --> 00:24:40.175
I am your mother.

311
00:24:46.148 --> 00:24:47.783
Let me see.

312
00:25:02.098 --> 00:25:03.465
I'm sorry.

313
00:25:06.735 --> 00:25:09.805
For saying you're my mother?

314
00:25:12.076 --> 00:25:13.475
No.

315
00:25:17.746 --> 00:25:20.015
For not asking you first

316
00:25:21.001 --> 00:25:24.953
whether you were good or bad.

317
00:25:26.734 --> 00:25:29.558
I had many opportunities to do it.

318
00:25:40.100 --> 00:25:41.870
I asked dad

319
00:25:43.767 --> 00:25:46.675
to stop going out with you.

320
00:25:48.677 --> 00:25:50.145
I'm...

321
00:25:51.068 --> 00:25:52.514
regretful

322
00:25:54.451 --> 00:25:55.918
Because?

323
00:25:57.804 --> 00:25:59.988
I dislike you,

324
00:26:02.068 --> 00:26:05.093
but I don't want dad to be sad.

325
00:26:09.260 --> 00:26:11.400
You don't like me either, right?

326
00:26:15.905 --> 00:26:18.874
Who likes someone who hates them?

327
00:26:23.445 --> 00:26:25.080
Hurts.

328
00:26:28.150 --> 00:26:30.352
Use protective equipment from now on.

329
00:26:31.889 --> 00:26:33.724
Well,

330
00:26:33.724 --> 00:26:35.424
That makes me look like a fool.

331
00:26:42.555 --> 00:26:44.266
I'm hungry.

332
00:26:46.604 --> 00:26:48.370
Shall we eat?

333
00:27:05.756 --> 00:27:07.289
Is it spicy?

334
00:27:08.826 --> 00:27:10.559
I want to get used to it.

335
00:27:12.862 --> 00:27:16.098
If you find it spicy, don't eat it.
Why do you do it?

336
00:27:18.082 --> 00:27:20.068
Because I want to get along

337
00:27:20.738 --> 00:27:22.371
with the people.

338
00:27:38.887 --> 00:27:40.822
Can I ask you something?

339
00:27:45.431 --> 00:27:47.801
Why did you name him Oscar?

340
00:27:47.801 --> 00:27:49.364
I mean the fish.

341
00:27:54.103 --> 00:27:55.804
Do I have to...

342
00:27:57.300 --> 00:27:58.840
tell you?

343
00:28:04.694 --> 00:28:06.715
It's the name...

344
00:28:08.867 --> 00:28:11.400
of a boy

345
00:28:11.400 --> 00:28:13.388
that bothered me in Germany.

346
00:28:15.259 --> 00:28:17.426
He was the boy I hated the most.

347
00:28:20.998 --> 00:28:22.933
Clear.

348
00:28:22.933 --> 00:28:24.433
I see.

349
00:28:26.638 --> 00:28:28.170
I'm sorry.

350
00:28:28.885 --> 00:28:30.772
I'll change the name.

351
00:28:33.464 --> 00:28:35.077
No.

352
00:28:36.958 --> 00:28:39.147
I like that name.

353
00:28:49.393 --> 00:28:50.992
Is it better now?

354
00:28:54.196 --> 00:28:55.764
Did the milk help?

355
00:28:55.764 --> 00:28:57.875
I hadn't tried it, but it's very good.

356
00:28:57.875 --> 00:28:59.635
Is it the first time?

357
00:28:59.635 --> 00:29:01.923
Didn't he ever buy it for you?

358
00:29:16.500 --> 00:29:18.620
It's very good, eat it.

359
00:29:27.767 --> 00:29:29.765
It's delicious.

360
00:29:29.765 --> 00:29:30.866
What are you doing?

361
00:29:30.866 --> 00:29:32.935
You only serve the guide.

362
00:29:32.935 --> 00:29:35.639
It is the dictatorship of the one who has the tweezers.

363
00:29:35.639 --> 00:29:37.927
I am not a dictator.

364
00:29:37.927 --> 00:29:39.267
Don't give me so much,

365
00:29:39.267 --> 00:29:40.811
Eat too, Jin Ho.

366
00:29:40.811 --> 00:29:41.987
That?

367
00:29:41.987 --> 00:29:44.388
- Eat.
- What's wrong with you two?

368
00:29:44.388 --> 00:29:46.248
What's happening?

369
00:29:46.248 --> 00:29:50.268
The way they look at each other is suspicious.

370
00:29:50.268 --> 00:29:51.153
One moment,

371
00:29:51.153 --> 00:29:54.901
Are you dating the guide?

372
00:29:54.901 --> 00:29:55.691
Sorry?

373
00:29:55.691 --> 00:29:57.926
He doesn't deny it.

374
00:29:57.926 --> 00:29:59.628
It just can't be!

375
00:29:59.628 --> 00:30:01.630
That?

376
00:30:02.166 --> 00:30:03.698
Oh really?

377
00:30:04.500 --> 00:30:06.568
- That?
- That?

378
00:30:06.568 --> 00:30:09.171
Yes, we are dating.

379
00:30:32.094 --> 00:30:34.129
Why don't you sing a song?

380
00:30:34.129 --> 00:30:36.832
I sing very badly, you better do it.

381
00:30:36.832 --> 00:30:38.751
Do you think you're at a concert?

382
00:30:38.751 --> 00:30:41.522
You pay the entrance or you sing. You choose!

383
00:30:42.806 --> 00:30:43.472
- No.
- Choose.

384
00:30:43.472 --> 00:30:44.908
Sing a song.

385
00:30:44.908 --> 00:30:47.008
It's my turn, I'm going to sing.

386
00:31:14.636 --> 00:31:16.305
Today you are very happy.

387
00:31:16.305 --> 00:31:18.075
Yes, I am.

388
00:31:18.075 --> 00:31:19.254
Excellent.

389
00:31:19.254 --> 00:31:21.510
We only took one trip together,

390
00:31:21.510 --> 00:31:22.903
but we keep meeting,

391
00:31:22.903 --> 00:31:24.646
We have fun and we support each other.

392
00:31:24.646 --> 00:31:27.182
The reason I'm so happy

393
00:31:27.182 --> 00:31:29.852
It's that we don't hide our relationship.

394
00:31:29.852 --> 00:31:32.214
we don't worry
because of what others would think.

395
00:31:32.214 --> 00:31:33.607
I agree.

396
00:31:35.392 --> 00:31:37.092
Ja Yeong...

397
00:31:38.267 --> 00:31:40.161
I have to ask you a favor.

398
00:31:41.023 --> 00:31:43.400
If you do me a favor first,

399
00:31:43.400 --> 00:31:45.900
I will listen to you.

400
00:31:47.438 --> 00:31:49.173
OK.

401
00:31:49.173 --> 00:31:50.939
Tell me and I will do it.

402
00:31:52.009 --> 00:31:55.179
Sing me a song.

403
00:31:55.179 --> 00:31:56.663
That?

404
00:31:56.663 --> 00:31:58.104
Impossible,

405
00:31:58.104 --> 00:31:59.184
I sing very badly.

406
00:31:59.184 --> 00:32:00.204
I won't do you the favor.

407
00:32:00.204 --> 00:32:02.252
Come on, it's not fair.

408
00:32:02.252 --> 00:32:04.252
What if I take you on a horseback ride?

409
00:32:04.722 --> 00:32:05.823
No.

410
00:32:05.823 --> 00:32:07.455
I sing very badly.

411
00:32:08.692 --> 00:32:10.292
Okay, but don't laugh.

412
00:32:11.133 --> 00:32:12.527
Now?

413
00:32:13.338 --> 00:32:15.096
Here?

414
00:32:15.931 --> 00:32:18.066
When and where else should I do it?

415
00:32:19.735 --> 00:32:21.472
Don't laugh.

416
00:32:21.472 --> 00:32:23.140
Promise me.

417
00:32:23.140 --> 00:32:24.472
I promise.

418
00:32:25.838 --> 00:32:27.542
<i>♪ Stay ♪</i>

419
00:32:29.344 --> 00:32:30.979
Don't laugh.

420
00:32:33.879 --> 00:32:37.118
<i>♪ Stay ♪</i>

421
00:32:38.100 --> 00:32:40.989
<i>♪ By my side ♪</i>

422
00:32:41.590 --> 00:32:43.892
<i>♪ Don't go ♪</i>

423
00:32:44.534 --> 00:32:47.696
<i>♪ Don't do it ♪</i>

424
00:32:52.701 --> 00:32:56.204
<i>♪ Longing is left behind ♪</i>

425
00:32:56.901 --> 00:33:00.575
<i>♪ On the long road ♪</i>

426
00:33:01.694 --> 00:33:05.480
<i>♪ You can't go back ♪</i>

427
00:33:05.480 --> 00:33:10.485
<i>♪ In search of the rainbow ♪</i>

428
00:34:15.434 --> 00:34:17.719
<i>♪ The cold wind ♪</i>

429
00:34:18.267 --> 00:34:22.267
<i>♪ Blow ♪</i>

430
00:34:22.267 --> 00:34:27.595
<i>♪ You cry alone ♪</i>

431
00:34:29.931 --> 00:34:34.534
<i>♪ But I will always be ♪</i>

432
00:34:34.534 --> 00:34:38.406
<i>♪ By your side ♪</i>

433
00:34:39.701 --> 00:34:45.547
<i>♪ I will never leave you ♪</i>

434
00:34:56.158 --> 00:34:58.128
I sing badly, right?

435
00:34:58.128 --> 00:34:59.504
No,

436
00:35:00.364 --> 00:35:01.996
I loved it.

437
00:35:04.168 --> 00:35:05.834
Oh really?

438
00:35:07.703 --> 00:35:09.104
Now tell me,

439
00:35:09.104 --> 00:35:12.242
I will grant you that favor.

440
00:35:13.534 --> 00:35:14.660
Well,

441
00:35:14.660 --> 00:35:16.444
Ja Yeong.

442
00:35:18.068 --> 00:35:19.647
You will see...

443
00:35:22.017 --> 00:35:24.119
Dinner with your family?

444
00:35:25.554 --> 00:35:28.826
If that seems too much to you,
we can wait a little longer.

445
00:35:28.826 --> 00:35:31.426
Why would it seem like too much?

446
00:35:33.662 --> 00:35:35.063
Oh really?

447
00:35:36.231 --> 00:35:38.633
So, bring Daniel.

448
00:35:38.633 --> 00:35:41.402
I told Dad and Jun Seo about Daniel.

449
00:35:42.720 --> 00:35:45.440
As long as Daniel wants to do it,

450
00:35:45.440 --> 00:35:47.275
We can all get together.

451
00:36:06.228 --> 00:36:08.463
Thanks for bringing me home.

452
00:36:09.531 --> 00:36:12.929
I should thank you today.

453
00:36:12.929 --> 00:36:15.837
Will you thank me and nothing more? Don't you forget something?

454
00:36:28.416 --> 00:36:30.652
Dad?

455
00:36:32.634 --> 00:36:34.054
Yes.

456
00:36:35.724 --> 00:36:37.100
Good evening, nice to meet you.

457
00:36:37.100 --> 00:36:38.793
Yes, hello.

458
00:36:42.497 --> 00:36:43.795
Dad.

459
00:36:43.795 --> 00:36:45.233
Yes.

460
00:36:45.233 --> 00:36:47.969
You should have called before coming.

461
00:36:49.555 --> 00:36:52.034
I had a meeting nearby

462
00:36:52.034 --> 00:36:53.875
and I passed by here.

463
00:36:58.513 --> 00:37:00.437
He is very handsome.

464
00:37:00.437 --> 00:37:02.150
- Yes.
- Made a good impression.

465
00:37:02.150 --> 00:37:04.285
Yes.

466
00:37:12.394 --> 00:37:14.862
- Take napkins.
- Thank you.

467
00:37:16.267 --> 00:37:17.866
I open it.

468
00:37:17.866 --> 00:37:19.698
He seems like a good guy.

469
00:37:19.698 --> 00:37:21.970
Yes it is.

470
00:37:26.801 --> 00:37:28.343
- Would you like...?
- Would you like...?

471
00:37:29.036 --> 00:37:29.911
You first.

472
00:37:29.911 --> 00:37:31.446
No, you first.

473
00:37:33.515 --> 00:37:35.650
Okay, me first.

474
00:37:37.452 --> 00:37:40.455
Would you like us to have dinner with Ja Yeong?
one of these days?

475
00:37:45.089 --> 00:37:46.928
Is it too soon?

476
00:37:48.029 --> 00:37:50.398
I don't want to pressure you. It's just that...

477
00:37:51.168 --> 00:37:52.600
I would love to.

478
00:37:55.537 --> 00:37:57.272
Let's have dinner.

479
00:37:58.540 --> 00:37:59.941
Are you sure?

480
00:38:02.980 --> 00:38:04.648
- Come in.
- Yes.

481
00:38:04.648 --> 00:38:05.745
Hey.

482
00:38:05.745 --> 00:38:06.967
That?

483
00:38:08.085 --> 00:38:09.786
It doesn't matter, come in.

484
00:38:09.786 --> 00:38:11.253
- Dad...
- Come in.

485
00:38:11.253 --> 00:38:14.455
- Well, hope you get home safely.
- Thank you.

486
00:38:28.098 --> 00:38:31.167
<i>This is a story of the Night Listener.</i>

487
00:38:31.167 --> 00:38:35.110
<i>"When I worked at dawn in a store,</i>

488
00:38:35.110 --> 00:38:37.367
<i>a client always came</i>

489
00:38:37.367 --> 00:38:39.314
<i>at the same time</i>

490
00:38:39.314 --> 00:38:42.901
<i>and with the same clothes
to buy the same beer."</i>

491
00:38:42.901 --> 00:38:44.185
What?

492
00:38:44.692 --> 00:38:46.734
<i>"He never spoke</i>

493
00:38:46.734 --> 00:38:49.223
<i>nor did he show any emotion.</i>

494
00:38:50.267 --> 00:38:51.753
<i>When I looked at her,</i>

495
00:38:51.753 --> 00:38:55.596
<i>I felt like I saw myself reflected in a mirror.</i>

496
00:38:59.935 --> 00:39:03.004
<i>I think the early morning is like that,</i>

497
00:39:03.838 --> 00:39:06.174
<i>it is a moment when you cannot hide anything.</i>

498
00:39:07.296 --> 00:39:11.760
<i>During the day,
We pretend to be happy or not feel alone.</i>

499
00:39:11.760 --> 00:39:15.116
<i>We can hide somewhere in between</i>

500
00:39:15.116 --> 00:39:19.022
<i>between happiness and loneliness.</i>

501
00:39:21.489 --> 00:39:23.725
<i>But it is not possible to do it at dawn.</i>

502
00:39:25.693 --> 00:39:29.597
<i>It is the moment when you know for sure</i>

503
00:39:30.966 --> 00:39:33.935
<i>that you are not at that intermediate point.</i>

504
00:39:37.072 --> 00:39:39.874
<i>- He didn't ask anything."
- He didn't ask anything.</i>

505
00:39:40.742 --> 00:39:43.111
<i>- "He didn't say anything."
- He didn't say anything.</i>

506
00:39:45.133 --> 00:39:47.415
<i>His presence was comforting.</i>

507
00:39:49.993 --> 00:39:52.487
<i>She stayed with me.</i>

508
00:39:53.734 --> 00:39:57.392
<i>Seeing her so similar to me,
I wanted to thank you...</i>

509
00:39:59.063 --> 00:40:00.697
<i>but I couldn't.</i>

510
00:40:02.197 --> 00:40:05.933
<i>He never bought beer again.</i>

511
00:40:10.745 --> 00:40:13.074
<i>I felt great relief.</i>

512
00:40:14.411 --> 00:40:17.478
<i>Surely, she doesn't feel so alone anymore.</i>

513
00:40:19.031 --> 00:40:20.715
<i>Thank you.</i>

514
00:40:22.190 --> 00:40:24.819
<i>If we meet again,</i>

515
00:40:25.334 --> 00:40:28.189
<i>I'll buy you a beer.</i>

516
00:41:07.734 --> 00:41:11.065
Didn't you say you didn't need anything?

517
00:41:12.100 --> 00:41:13.134
Yes.

518
00:41:13.134 --> 00:41:14.601
I said that.

519
00:41:14.601 --> 00:41:17.839
That was just a week ago,
just one week.

520
00:41:17.839 --> 00:41:20.041
Are you suddenly going to do it now?

521
00:41:21.598 --> 00:41:24.345
I thought I didn't need anything,

522
00:41:25.034 --> 00:41:27.381
But I realized something important.

523
00:41:29.884 --> 00:41:33.788
I saw you too sensitive
for a career in science and engineering.

524
00:41:36.124 --> 00:41:37.225
I'm sorry.

525
00:41:37.225 --> 00:41:40.497
Isn't it embarrassing

526
00:41:40.497 --> 00:41:42.497
retract like this?

527
00:41:44.203 --> 00:41:45.667
It's shameful,

528
00:41:45.667 --> 00:41:47.007
yes.

529
00:41:48.133 --> 00:41:50.771
Should I consider this effort?

530
00:41:51.439 --> 00:41:55.443
It is very difficult to be fair.

531
00:41:56.111 --> 00:41:57.300
Excuse me,

532
00:41:57.300 --> 00:41:58.664
And Professor Park's announcement?

533
00:41:58.664 --> 00:42:01.182
- I sent it to print a while ago.
- Good.

534
00:42:01.182 --> 00:42:02.383
- Marketing.
- Yes.

535
00:42:02.383 --> 00:42:03.844
Did you check the interview schedule?

536
00:42:03.844 --> 00:42:04.794
I'm on it.

537
00:42:04.794 --> 00:42:06.454
Hurry up!

538
00:42:06.454 --> 00:42:07.755
Yeah!

539
00:42:08.656 --> 00:42:11.726
<i>I decided to resume the internship.</i>

540
00:42:12.503 --> 00:42:16.330
<i>It was thanks to you then
and it's thanks to you now.</i>

541
00:42:39.034 --> 00:42:41.088
Where is the <i>ssamjang</i>?

542
00:42:41.767 --> 00:42:43.224
Here it is.

543
00:42:45.059 --> 00:42:47.395
Raphael!

544
00:42:51.335 --> 00:42:52.800
Hello.

545
00:42:53.835 --> 00:42:55.400
Father,

546
00:42:55.400 --> 00:42:56.767
How strange to see you here.

547
00:42:56.767 --> 00:42:58.072
Yes.

548
00:42:58.072 --> 00:43:01.734
We will take the father
to visit a new parishioner.

549
00:43:01.734 --> 00:43:02.346
I see.

550
00:43:02.346 --> 00:43:04.445
How have you been?

551
00:43:05.348 --> 00:43:08.419
Thanks to your prayers, I'm fine.

552
00:43:08.419 --> 00:43:11.119
You look much better.

553
00:43:11.119 --> 00:43:13.888
You must be at peace now.

554
00:43:13.888 --> 00:43:15.425
Yes, thanks to all of you.

